Fill in the required fields.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Recommended Certificate Authority: &lt;strong&gt;Google Public CA&lt;/strong&gt;. Let’s Encrypt may issue untrusted certificates in some cases (&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://myssl.com/&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34; &gt;Check Here&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;span style=&#34;white-space: nowrap;&#34;&gt;&lt;svg width=&#34;.7em&#34; height=&#34;.7em&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 21 21&#34;
        xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;
        &lt;path d=&#34;m13 3l3.293 3.293l-7 7l1.414 1.414l7-7L21 11V3z&#34; fill=&#34;currentColor&#34; /&gt;
        &lt;path d=&#34;M19 19H5V5h7l-2-2H5c-1.103 0-2 .897-2 2v14c0 1.103.897 2 2 2h14c1.103 0 2-.897 2-2v-5l-2-2v7z&#34;
            fill=&#34;currentColor&#34;&gt;
    &lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For Google CA, EAB credentials are required during initial setup.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://certd.docmirror.cn/guide/use/google/&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34; &gt;EAB Setup Guide&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;span style=&#34;white-space: nowrap;&#34;&gt;&lt;svg width=&#34;.7em&#34; height=&#34;.7em&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 21 21&#34;
